Dialogue: 10,0:00:01.00,0:00:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcome the cast and staff.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:03.00,0:00:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give them a big round of applause!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:15.18,0:00:18.58,Top,,0,0,0,,First, the original author of this work.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:18.58,0:00:21.79,Top,,0,0,0,,Please welcome Ebina Kayoko-san!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:26.64,0:00:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she played her role well and beautifully with her voice,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.54,0:00:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,making Kayoko into a really believable character. {?????? no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:00:43.06,0:00:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Kayo-chan, voiced by her,\N is really cute and loveable.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:49.58,0:00:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She is adorable.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:51.74,0:00:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like the young people
Dialogue: 10,0:00:55.32,0:01:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to know about the destructive \NMarch 10th air raid too.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:01.47,0:01:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I could do it through media,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:03.16,0:01:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'm most grateful to be able\N to participate in the creation of this.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.52,0:01:14.23,Top,,0,0,0,,Well, I voiced Kayoko-san. I am Ueto Aya.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:14.23,0:01:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this is the second time \NI've been given such a major role.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:20.55,0:01:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried my best to express \NKayoko's soft and gentle voice.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:30.24,0:01:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And well, I strove for that effect, \Nwhen you're sucked straight into the screen.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.41,0:01:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And I hope you won't find\N the pace of this film uneven.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.04,0:01:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When I looked at the finished product, I found myself \Ncriticizing my acting quite a lot. It was stressful.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.35,0:01:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And you thought so too. Right? Right? Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.85,0:01:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this was Kayoko.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.61,0:02:07.43,Top,,0,0,0,,Well, before I actually looked into\N {\i1}Half a Sweet Potato{\i0}, what it's about...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.23,0:02:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I met with Ebina-san \Nand her daughter Yasuha-chan. {????? no clue why he says ebina's mother if she died in air raid, but she has a daugher yasuha so i guess that's what he means???}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.32,0:02:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And it made me realize it's about enduring hardships with a pure heart. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:17.60,0:02:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tried to match that theme as best I could.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:22.22,0:02:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wrote this music with the poem Ebina's mother wrote in mind. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:32.32,0:02:39.20,Top,,0,0,0,,Before watching this movie, when I learned I was going to sing the theme song, I hesitated a lot.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.20,0:02:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered, "What feelings should I put into it? \NHow do I go about it?"
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.36,0:02:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had my grandma tell me \Na lot of stories about the war.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.84,0:02:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, before this, I watched \Nthe film {\i1}Who's Left Behind{\i0}. {ushiro no shoumen daare}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.28,0:02:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, I've been watching that film \Nat home since I was little.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.42,0:03:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've watched it once more, diligently, \Nto see if there was something I'd missed.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.68,0:03:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because no matter how many times I watch it \Nor how many times I listen to it,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.72,0:03:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it really touches my heart, and I can't stop crying.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.53,0:03:20.88,Top,,0,0,0,,Hello, everyone. My name is Miyake, and I am the chairman of the Production Committee.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.42,0:03:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not really a big shot in the movie industry,
Dialogue: 10,0:03:24.54,0:03:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but Ayabe from Route Pictures, far in the back, has been my friend for many years. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.06,0:03:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was around October 2003 when he said
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.40,0:03:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,he definitely wanted to adapt \N{\i1}Half a Sweet Potato{\i0} into a movie.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.30,0:03:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So the president was very invested in it. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.10,0:03:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, if we don't release it now, the next anniversary will be in ten years—the 70th one.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:46.04,0:03:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And there'd be very few people who'd actually lived through it.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:49.41,0:03:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We realized this is our last chance to express our respect. I felt that too, so we all worked hard. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:53.82,0:03:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm glad to have worked on this.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.39,0:04:04.33,Top,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you very much. And I really think that everyone's thoughts are with Ebina-san today. {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.33,0:04:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope everyone enjoys it today. \NThat would make me really happy. Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.79,0:04:19.94,Top,,0,0,0,,This movie, or rather the original work, moved\N the 2.5 million people who read it, not just us. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:19.94,0:04:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we wanted even more people to learn\N about this story. This was what motivated us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:26.17,0:04:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, today, please enjoy this premier showing of {\i1}Tomorrow Will Be Better{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:32.52,0:04:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.33,0:04:46.54,Top,,0,0,0,,When I first watched it, \NI felt relieved. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.24,0:04:56.09,Top,,0,0,0,,Even though, in a way, it made me relive once again all those painful, grueling experiences.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.09,0:05:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But it also made me glad I'm alive. \NI survived to fight another day.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:02.23,0:05:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It reinforced my belief that you only live once,\N and I'm really glad to be alive right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.70,0:05:13.86,Top,,0,0,0,,I also have a big brother \Nwho is just two years older than me.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.86,0:05:18.00,Top,,0,0,0,,And well, while listening to this anime's voices...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.00,0:05:23.74,Top,,0,0,0,,While watching this anime, I couldn't help comparing Kisaburo to my real-life older brother.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.74,0:05:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, I just looked at the screen for a moment \Nand almost burst into tears.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.27,0:05:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But soon I got used to how it looks,\N to watching it, and to the voices in it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.42,0:05:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this story is really about family love,\N which is the most important thing ever.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.53,0:05:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that regard, I think it's best for as many people as possible to see it,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:48.26,0:05:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe start cherishing family love more.\N That would make me very happy.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.04,0:05:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how I felt about this movie.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.98,0:06:05.49,Top,,0,0,0,,We really wanted to convey Ebina-san's feelings \Nas a Great Tokyo Air Raid survivor.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.49,0:06:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo was no more,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.99,0:06:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but she didn't give in to despair, and she also tried to inspire others not to lose heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.00,0:06:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you'll also feel that way \Nafter you've watched it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.43,0:06:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As a storyteller, I would like as many people as possible to watch it.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.49,0:06:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.79,0:06:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:30.58,0:06:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we celebrate the screening of the movie today, \Nwe'd like to present the staff with some gifts. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.01,0:06:39.37,Top,,0,0,0,,Please welcome the Hayashiya family!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:47.28,0:06:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please accept these flowers.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:54.63,0:06:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.72,0:07:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and that concludes today's stage greeting from the staff!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:20.11,0:07:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A round of applause, please! Thank you!
